{:proof/problem-id "apm-t94J01", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (plan and alignment explicitly reference topological spaces, connectedness, and ladder-connected covers) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (the Lean target is an “iff” with hypotheses spelled out before the conclusion) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (the formal target fully states the equivalence) · notes: helper lemma focuses on the “connected ⇒ ladder-connected” direction via the component cover.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Show that ladder connectedness (any open cover admits a finite chain linking two points) is equivalent to connectedness.\"\n :terms [{:name \"ladder chain\"\n          :meaning \"A finite sequence of open sets with consecutive overlaps joining p to q.\"\n          :needed-because \"This is the object we must relate to connected components.\"}\n         {:name \"open cover by components\"\n          :meaning \"Use the connected components themselves as the open cover.\"\n          :needed-because \"If ladder connectedness holds, applying it to this cover shows the whole space sits inside one component.\"}\n         {:name \"Lebesgue-number style compactness argument\"\n          :meaning \"Given disconnect, exploit separation to build cover with no ladder between points in different components.\"\n          :needed-because \"Provides the converse: if the space is disconnected, some cover forbids a ladder.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"Definitions of connectedness/components; properties of open covers; finite chain arguments.\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Prove (⇒) by contradiction: if X were disconnected, take the open cover by the two clopen pieces; no ladder can cross the gap. Prove (⇐) by taking the component cover and showing any ladder forces the two points to lie in the same component, so there is only one component.\"\n             :why-this-now \"Directly mirrors the informal combinatorial notion and avoids heavier tools.\"\n             :lean-target \"ApmCanaries.Frames.T94J01.Apm_v2_t94J01_1775010781379.connected_iff_ladderConnected\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Mathlib has connectedness/component notions; ladder connectedness will likely need a custom definition.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done\n                :stage2 :done\n                :stage3 :in-progress\n                :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"A topological space is connected iff it is ladder connected.\"\n             :formal-name \"connected_iff_ladderConnected\"\n             :formal-target\n             \"∀ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X],\n                IsConnected (Set.univ : Set X) ↔ LadderConnectedSpace X\"\n             :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                            :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                            :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                            :notes \"This theorem exactly matches the problem statement once ladder connectedness is defined.\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"connected_iff_ladderConnected\"\n               :formal-statement\n               \"∀ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X],\n                  IsConnected (Set.univ : Set X) ↔ LadderConnectedSpace X\"\n               :informal-clause \"Equates the new ladder notion with ordinary connectedness.\"\n               :role :main-theorem}\n              {:formal-name \"ladderConnected_of_connected_components_cover\"\n               :formal-statement\n               \"∀ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X],\n                  IsConnected (Set.univ : Set X) →\n                  LadderConnectedSpace X\"\n               :informal-clause \"Uses the open-cover-by-components argument to produce ladders.\"\n               :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\n**Summary.**\n- Stage 1 of `/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94J01/apm-v2-t94J01-177501078